  "prompt": "Mumbai law college?",
  "response": "Mumbai Law College, officially known as **Government Law College (GLC), Mumbai**, is one of the oldest and most prestigious law schools in India. Established in **1855**, it is located in **Churchgate, Mumbai**, and is affiliated with the **University of Mumbai**. Here are some key details about the college:\n\n---\n\n### **Programs Offered**\n1. **Bachelor of Laws (LL.B.)** \u2013 3-year program  \n2. **Bachelor of Arts, Bachelor of Laws (B.A. LL.B.)** \u2013 5-year integrated program  \n3. **Master of Laws (LL.M.)** \u2013 2-year program  \n4. Diploma and certificate courses in specialized areas of law\n\n---\n\n### **Admission Process**\n- **Eligibility**:  \n  - For LL.B.: Graduate degree in any discipline with a minimum of 45% marks.  \n  - For B.A. LL.B.: Passed 10+2 or equivalent with a minimum of 45% marks.  \n- **Entrance Exam**: Admissions are based on the **CET (Common Entrance Test)** conducted by the Directorate of Higher Education, Maharashtra.  \n\n---\n\n### **Reputation and Alumni**\n- GLC Mumbai has produced several prominent legal professionals, judges, politicians, and leaders, including **Dr. B.R. Ambedkar**, **Nani Palkhivala**, and **Fali Nariman**.  \n- It is known for its strong academic curriculum, moot court competitions, and placement opportunities in top law firms and corporate legal departments.\n\n---\n\n### **Campus and Facilities**\n- The college is located in the heart of Mumbai, offering easy access to courts, law firms, and legal institutions.  \n- Facilities include a **library**, **moot court halls**, **hostels**, and legal aid clinics.\n\n---\n\n### **Why Choose GLC Mumbai?**\n- Legacy and reputation in legal education.  \n- Strong alumni network.  \n- Exposure to the legal industry in Mumbai, a hub for corporate and litigation practice.\n\n---\n\nFor more details, you can visit the official website: **[Government Law College, Mumbai](https://glcmumbai.com)**. Let me know if you need further assistance!",
